## Intro {#intro}

When creating a web app with the Flatlogic Generator, the recommended input is a clear and concise description of your application, ideally in the form of user stories. User stories typically follow a structure like "As a \[user role\], I want to \[goal\] so that \[reason\]." This helps in defining the features and functionalities you need. For example, you might say, "As a manager, I want to track employee performance so that I can provide timely feedback." This helps the generator understand what key components and features your app should have.

## Brief  {#brief}

Order product directly from the producer and pick it up at an agreed location.   
Producers get online orders of his products. Producer delivers onsite products directly to the customers on an agreed public location.

## Subscription Model {#subscription-model}

- Fremium \- Producers can try full features for 1 month  
- Monthly / Yearly membership for unlocking more features and unlimited products  
  - Admin can change pricing   
- Use stripe for subscription model 

Benefits

| Producers | Customers |
| :---- | :---- |
| Can increase or adjust stock and plan sales better | Can purchase products directly from producer Can pickup products at their convenient location or at home |

## Mobile version features {#mobile-version-features}

### Registration {#registration}

Same features as web version

### On spot sales {#on-spot-sales}

Customers and producer come to an agreed location. Customers opens mobile application and show QRCode for his order to producer. Producer scan this Qrcode and reads what kind of items were ordered by customers. Customer pays for items and gets products. Producer slides order as delivered and paid and serves the next customer, again scans QRCode. 

- If a customer does not have QRCode then its possible to search for an order with a mobile number or email address

## Web version features {#web-version-features}

### Landing page {#landing-page}

Landing page shows a video on full screen showing how farmers grow his vegetables on the land and add his ready products to store. Then the video shows how farmers sell products to regular people in public locations. Use a parking place as an example.

### Registration {#registration-1}

Use supabase authorization solution.  
Minimum acceptance criteria are logins with Gmail, Facebook,Instagram

Registration starts with selecting an option how the user wants to register

- Producer  
- Customer


Registration is done with a steps where user see the progress. It should be easy to follow and user has to get impression that steps does not take long time to complete.

#### Producer registration  {#producer-registration}

Registration workflow ensures that the user fills mandatory preferences.

1st step

- User fills personal information  
  - Mobile number  
  - Username   
  - Address  
  - Name of business entities  
  - Link social account to the account  
    - Facebook  
    - Instagram  
    - Gmail

2nd step

- User fills items interested to sale/purchase  
- Selects or created preferred locations from the map 

3rd steps

- Fills virtual items store. Here provides items quantity, price per item.

By completing registration its ensures that the user is ready to create his first event to sell products.

#### Customer registration {#customer-registration}

Similar to producer registration, 3rd step virtual items store is skipped.

### Event search {#event-search}

As a login customer on the dashboard page can search events based on advanced criteria and create an order.

Advanced criteria \- producer, location, items 

### Create a new event {#create-a-new-event}

As a logged producer with completed registration and configured virtual store, can easily create a new event using an app that  is automatically shared on other linked social media accounts. 

As a logged producer who created an event, can see the created events and monitor orders with quantity.

### Preferences {#preferences}

#### Referrals  {#referrals}

As a user who navigates to his preference page, can easily copy and share referral link and invite new users to the application.  
A user who shares his referral link and navigates to the preference page can see how many referral links were used for new completed registration.

#### Favourite producers {#favourite-producers}

As a logged user who navigates to his preference page, can see the list of favourite producers. Users can add, remove producers from the list.

#### Favourite products {#favourite-products}

As a logged user who navigates to his preference page, can see the list of favourite products. Users can add, remove products from the list.

#### Favourite locations {#favourite-locations}

As a logged user who navigates to his preference page, can see the list of favourite locations. Users can add, remove locations from the list.

### Virtual store {#virtual-store}

As a producer registered to the application can view or edit virtual store.  
Store is a physical overview of products available for sale for a producer.  
For example, a producer purchases 100 kg of apples that wants to sell in upcoming days. His available store quantity is 100 kg 

|  |  |
| :---- | :---- |
| Name | Name of item E.g apples |
| Image | Item image |
| Available quantity | E.g. 10 kg, 10 liters, 10 pc |
| Unit price | 10 euro per kg, liter, pc |
| Status | Available Blocked for event  100 kg oranges are available, producer creates an event where we wants to sale 20 kg, then  80 kg are available   20 kg are blocked After sales event is done and all items are sold, then store has 80 kg available oranges   |

### Order {#order}

As a registered user or unregistered visitor can search on website for events and create an order. In case a visitor is unregistered, before placing an order has to complete registration. 

| Order items  | Total items that were ordered |
| :---- | :---- |
| Total Price |  |
| Purchase status | Ordered Confirmed Paid Completed |

Order status

- Ordered \- customer creates an order   
- Confirmed \- producer confirms order and user receives notification  
- Completed \- when a user comes to the location and exchange items for money, and producer marks order as delivered, then order change status to paid and completed  
- User paid but the product was not delivered. Will not be supported in this version

## User stories {#user-stories}

### Registration {#registration-3}

1. User navigates to website  
2. User click on register   
3. User selects option from registration options  
   1. Socials \- Facebook, Instagram, Gmail, Email   
4. User selects type of registration  
   1. Producer  
   2. User  
5. Based on selection in step 4 user completes registration and his profile and preferences 

Mandatory registration data for the user

| Producer | User |
| :---- | :---- |
| Business name | username |
| Business address | Adress |
| Preferred sales locations \- at least one | Preferred pick up location Location radius  Favourite producers Favourite items |
| Sell items  |  |
| Virtual store  |  |

### Virtual store for producer  {#virtual-store-for-producer}

- Producer list all available items with quantity and price  available for sale   
- If producer creates a event or sell the product, this store will picture the current status of available items   
- Items  
  - Product name  
  - Quantity  pc, kg, l  
  - Sell price per item   
    

### Profile \- Producer {#profile---producer}

1. Producer is asked to fill his profile   
   1. Address  
   2. Logo  
   3. Description  
   4. Socials  
      1. Instagram  
      2. Facebook  
           
2. Producer purchase subscription   
3. Producer is asked to select products that he wants to sell  
4. Producer is asked to update information about store \- items available for sale  
5. Producer uploads logo and pictures about products to his gallery.   
   

### Ready to sell \- creating a new event {#ready-to-sell---creating-a-new-event}

6. Producers creates a new sales event and fill required information 

**Precondition**

- Profile is completed  
- Preferences are completed  
- Virtual store is completed with items ready to sale 

  1. Selects products from virtual store with  quantity and unit price available for sale   
  2. Selects or creates event name   
  3. Selects or creates  event location   
  4. Sales event start date   
  5. Sales event start time   
  6. Sales event end time    
  7. Event picture from gallery  
  8. Fill event preferences  
     1. Minimum order per customer	  
     2. Payment method \- default cash

     

7. Producer sets status for event  
   1. Publish  
   2. Draft   
8. Producer in one click shares published event on social media defined in user preferences.  
     
   Share image  contains   
   1. event link   
   2. QRCode  with event link decoded   
   3. Sales event name   
   4. Products for sale with price   
   5. Image from gallery   
   6.  Start Date and time   
   7. End Date and time 

### Creating an order  {#creating-an-order}

1. User receives shared event link/url from producers from social media post, for example Facebook  
   1. Or user receives notification in web application   
2. User navigates to event url website  
3. User selects quantity from product list   
4. Before completing an order user is asked to login or register using social accounts  
5. User is loggin and order is completed  
6. Producer is notified my email about a new order   
7. Producer confirms order by changing the status or order to confirmed 

### Exchange of goods  {#exchange-of-goods}

1. Producer comes to agreed location and notifies all customers that he is on the place   
2. Customer comes on agreed place and meets produce

      3\.	User shows in mobile app QRCode for his order to producer   
      4\.  Producer scans QRCode and reads order details   
      5\.  Producers handle over products to the uses, accepts payment and set order as     
completed 

### User search sales event and create a purchase  {#user-search-sales-event-and-create-a-purchase}

For example

Producer  has 100 kg of oranges in store. We wants to create 2 sales events and sell 50kg of oranges in 2 events, on 2 different places in different day and time 

6\. Producer shares event on selected social networks Facebook and Instagram.   
This share contains also QR Code with link to  download mobile application and register account 

* Facebook   
* Instagram

7\. Producer activates the sales event and starts to receive orders from customers.

   
This QR code contains a link to a specific event and only registered users can create and order.  
If an user scans this QRCode it will be asked for registration in the application

* Producer confirms all orders and customers receives a mobile notification   
* Producer sends mobile notification to customers 1 day before the sales event   
* Producer comes with products on defined place   
  * Producer sends mobile notification with information that he is on the place   
* Sale Process on the place   
  * Producer ask customer for a QRCode of the order   
  * Producer logs into app and from this app scans a QRCode   
    * After scanning he can see the order details   
      * Name of customer  
      * Ordered product/s and quantity  
          
* Producer gives products to the customer and in application slides order as delivered   
  * Producer has an option to manually update order with new product or modify the quantity  
* Producer sold all the products and left the place.
